messages.message: is it reasonable for me to respond that we're investigating? I know with the criss-cross stuff that there may not be bandwidth to really look into this right now
It does look like they have some kind of workaround right now
> I was able to to successfully upload the documents that Instabase was complaining about when I uploaded them with a smaller group of files or by itself
yeah this sounds time sensitive, so I would suggest uploading in smaller batches
there’s also a “new uploader” option when they upload. they could try that.
we’ve had this problem uploading a large # of docs to instabase for a while now. not something that’s ever been high pri enough to tackle.
I think new uploader is the default so they're probably already using that

Okay, for now I'll suggest the workaround, let them know it's on our radar, and try to get a better understanding as to whether this is a one-off activity for them, or if it's a workflow they want to keep using
